                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-04-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay states that he will be absent from Washington for a month, but can
                    always be reached by telegraph.</p>
                <p>Much is necessarily left to Mr. Rockhill’s discretion; he is instructed to favor
                    moderation both in amount and terms of payment. This Government thinks increased
                    privileges and administrative reforms are more desirable than a large cash
                    indemnity.</p>
                <p>All that has been done by Mr. Rockhill is cordially approved.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
